<h2 id="lessons" class="font-semibold text-xl mb-2">Lessons Learned</h2>
<ol class="list-decimal list-inside mt-2">
  <li>Use meeting time for decisions, not dicussions.</li>
  <li>Organization is flexible, and should suit your needs. Focus on ease of use, not perfection.</li>
</ol>

<h3 id="learned" class="font-semibold mt-4">How We Learned This</h3>
<h4>Lesson 1</h4>
  <p class="ml-8">We often did not get to all of our planned points during meetings, and we struggled to collaborate when there was too much discussion. Lack of proper check-ins made us feel like we were not making progress on things.
</p>
<h4>Lesson 2</h4>
  <p class="ml-8">We were open to organizational changes to make documentation, communication, and organization more accessible to all team members. We saw these tools as living rather than set in stone.</p>
